Professional healthcare workers wearing personal protective equipment (PPE) make their way to tents dedicated to the treatment of possible COVID-19 coronavirus patients in Pretoria. JOHANNESBURG - The health department has reported a further 345 COVID-19 related deaths. This brings the death toll in South Africa to 8,884. More than 100 people died in Gauteng, 97 in the Western Cape, 89 in KZN, and 43 in the Eastern Cape. SA's recovery rate is now close to 70%. Less than 4,000 new cases have been confirmed in the last 24-hours. READ: Threat of a COVID-19 generation This is the lowest number since the last week of June. More than half of the new cases are from KZN and Gauteng. Health Media Release 4 August 2020 (1) by eNCA.com on Scribd  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.